In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 22, 2011, as National Maritime Day in the United States. He highlights the importance of the United States Merchant Marine in keeping the nation safe and prosperous, connecting businesses and citizens around the world. He acknowledges the historical significance of the SS Savannah completing the first successful voyage by a steam-powered ship across the Atlantic in 1819. During World War II, the Merchant Marines played a critical role in providing supplies to troops abroad, but suffered a high death rate. The article also emphasizes the continued importance of the maritime industry in providing skilled employment and contributing to the economy. President Obama calls upon the people of the United States to observe National Maritime Day by displaying the flag and requests that ships sailing under the American flag dress ship on that day.